HEADWORD: Zikkurat
<hw>Zik"ku*rat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A temple tower of
the Babylonians or Assyrians, consisting of a lofty pyramidal structure,
built in successive stages, with outside staircases, and a shrine at the
top; -- called also <altname>ziggurat</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

